Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje has extended the shutdown of civil service activities for the next two week.
 
Ganduje announced the two-weeks extension on Monday while receiving a report of COVID-19 Fundraising Committee at Government house.
 
The Governor said the extension of the stay-at-home directive became imperative following the increasing number of cases of COVID- 19 being recorded daily in the country.   To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .